race.comment: OCEANELLA (9) looks ready to win. Two runs back have been good, finding the line nicely for a runner-up finish on each occasion. She got too far back fresh from a wide gate and just missed, good again at Mornington last time. Now to 1300m in what looks a fairly winnable affair, she can break through. FORT OF DREAMS (4) has been solid in two runs to date and will be better for them. He draws for a soft trail and should get his chance. SWEET FARNAN (14) has been good either side of a heavy track flop at Stony Creek. She's a speedy type who will bounce to the front and take catching. OLYMPIAD (17) resumes for his second campaign and could be an improver this time in.
